(WIP)

Assumes kubeconfig is in ~/.kube/config.

Run ./run-kwok.sh in the background.
Run latency.go in another tab.
Deploy generated/kwok-nodes onto your cluster.
Metrics are exported to http://localhost:2112/metrics
Save prometheus.yml and run your local prometheus e.g. `./prometheus  --web.listen-address="0.0.0.0:9091"`

`./prometheus --storage.tsdb.path=data/ --web.enable-admin-api --web.listen-address="0.0.0.0:9091` (for snapshots?)


# For Podman login

sudo apt-get install podman -y

# GET ACR creds
az acr credential show --name acnpublic 

returns:
{
  "passwords": [
    {
      "name": "password",
      "value": "pass1"
    },
    {
      "name": "password2",
      "value": "pass2"
    }
  ],
  "username": "acnpublic"
}

# Login to ACR through podman
podman login acnpublic.azurecr.io -u acnpublic -p <pass>